HEADWORD: Sigmoidal
<hw>Sig*moid"al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/<?/<?/; <?/<?/<?/ sigma
+ <grk>e'i^dos</grk> form, likeness: cf. F.
<ets>sigmo⟦ium⟧de</ets>.]</ety> <def>Curved in two directions, like the
letter S, or the Greek ⟦sigmat⟧.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sigmoid flexure</b></col> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>, <cd>the
last curve of the colon before it terminates in the rectum.</cd> --
<col><b>Sigmoid valves</b></col>. <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <cd>See
<cref>Semilunar valves</cref>, under <er>Semilunar</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
